	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Personally ,despite what a lot of people say, I think that when soloing earth is THE WORST pet to use. It is also the WORST PET when grouping. I have never yet found a good use for this pet exept just before a spell level when the extra HP is a must for the pet to survive. If you need a pet to keep a mob off of you so you can nuke, the air pet works just fine because the stuns generate a huge taunt effect. Also air pets are a lot more efficient during down time beause yo do not need to waste mana healing them. The water pet has been great while sosoing so far as well, it hits hard and has very god HP, and lasts longer in a fight then an earth because it actually has some agility. I have not really used fire much yet, but I hear that they are awesome at higher levels<br>Just my thoughts</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
